      "full_name": "The 924th Unmanned Aerial Vehicle Center (Military Unit 20924)",
      "is_primary": true
    }
  ],
  "remarks": "The 924th Unmanned Aerial Vehicle Center (Military Unit 20924) is part of the Russian Ministry of Defence. Servicemen are being trained at the Center to complete the unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) companies being formed in the Western and Central Military Districts. At the same time, the Center is engaged in the completion of military tests of complexes with UAVs (Zastava, Navodchik-2, Forpost and Orlan-10), which, upon completion of the tests, are transferred to UAV companies. The 924th Unmanned Aerial Vehicle Center of the Russian Ministry of Defence trains UAV operators for the Armed Forces of the Russian Federation. Many of them have taken part in combat operations in the North Caucasus, Syria, and are now in the zone of the Special Military Operation.",
  "@context": "https://www.ammitto.org/ontology/context.jsonld"
}